<subSubSection id="446E2CB5342AACB81117876E09F551FB" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="251EE0E0C883B5647C999EF3B05EAA11" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="272566077170035701650A8A753C0A5A" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
In the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="FF28E0D00E5551E4B86DC2BED285D846" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena hilaris subsp. nigriventris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hilaris" subSpecies="nigriventris">Zygaena hilaris nigriventris</taxonomicName>
it is stated, 'This subspecies can be distinguished from subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="2F0F7D85FE4A90E47C04DC99BE48FF77" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena apocrypha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="apocrypha" subSpecies="apocrypha">apocrypha</taxonomicName>
Le Charles from the area around Nice essentially by the abdomen with its black ventral side and absence of whitish rings. Also wingspan is greater on average.' This taxon differs greatly from the nominal taxon 
<taxonomicName id="EFC7CD77203902606DAF6FF5063EC65E" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena apocrypha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="apocrypha" subSpecies="apocrypha">apocrypha</taxonomicName>
, as this was described as a subspecies of and is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="72015C5C0E649B3B801E74065CD83821" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena fausta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fausta">Zygaena fausta</taxonomicName>
from the Alpes-de-Haute-Provence; currently it is placed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C410D66E51C95D2E94FC1CD18BE9DEDC" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena fausta subsp. fausta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fausta" subSpecies="fausta">Zygaena fausta fausta</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1767) (
<bibRefCitation id="72E661AF236B4E76D1E5CB1720894053" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
: 103). 
<bibRefCitation id="263E1A3DB3299EC198E10E884ECEBB26" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012)</bibRefCitation>
most likely confused the names 
<taxonomicName id="CFB86BA7EA4D731D33CE9CF1DE0A47D1" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena apocrypha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="apocrypha" subSpecies="apocrypha">apocrypha</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D9B2721FDDDD9FD28427AC5E20C14603" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena chrysophaea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="chrysophaea" subSpecies="chrysophaea">chrysophaea</taxonomicName>
, the latter taxon being a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="A4B6A7C53DF561DC3B369758826AE5A2" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena hilaris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">Zygaena hilaris</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7D575967C13BF8710105A07E340B4A8" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName id="A60D1031DC4157BA9ABF232DC09C1BD5" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena hilaris subsp. chrysophaea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hilaris" subSpecies="chrysophaea">Zygaena hilaris chrysophaea</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution in France, ranging from Vaucluse, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, 
<normalizedToken id="4F6DFE6B668B8EE0DA38C594FEF95F20" originalValue="Drôme">Drome</normalizedToken>
and Hautes-Alpes to 
<normalizedToken id="D4CDAFA4EF8524D44F8C744829CDF242" originalValue="Isère">Isere</normalizedToken>
. To describe a subspecific taxon from within that distributional range cannot be justified; therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="05D788A064B4BE5FC95797D04A976391" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena hilaris subsp. nigriventris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hilaris" subSpecies="nigriventris">Zygaena hilaris nigriventris</taxonomicName>
is here formally placed as a synonym (syn. n.) of 
<taxonomicName id="81BDD5754326188013404053BCED8A92" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena hilaris subsp. chrysophaea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hilaris" subSpecies="chrysophaea">Zygaena hilaris chrysophaea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
